2.3 Match Block

The match block determines which privacy declarations a policy applies to. All top-level dimensions are AND'd together.

Built-in dimensions match against explicit fides_key values in the declaration:

Dimension

Matches Against

data_category

Declaration's data_categories list

data_use

Declaration's data_use value

data_subject

Declaration's data_subjects list

Custom taxonomy dimensions match based on taxonomy elements applied to declaration values via TaxonomyUsage. The key is the taxonomy_type of a registered custom taxonomy.

Match operators:

Operator

Behavior

any

Matches if any declaration value matches any listed value

all

Matches only if all listed values are present in the declaration

Note on all with single-valued fields: data_use is a single value per declaration (not a list). Using all with multiple values on data_use will never match since a declaration has exactly one data_use. The all operator is most useful with list-valued fields like data_categories and data_subjects.

Hierarchical matching: A value of user.contact matches user.contact.email (child) but not user (parent). This applies to both built-in dimensions and custom taxonomy elements that use hierarchical keys.

Taxonomy key collision prevention: Custom taxonomy taxonomy_type values must not collide with the reserved dimension names (data_category, data_use, data_subject). This is enforced at taxonomy creation time, not at policy authoring time.

Empty match: match: {} matches all declarations. Used for catch-all default policies.

2.4 Unless Block

The unless block defines conditions that, when met, invert the policy's decision:

ALLOW + unless triggered = access denied (decisive — evaluation stops)

DENY + unless triggered = denial suppressed (not decisive — evaluation continues to next policy)

This behavior is intentionally asymmetric. An ALLOW that inverts to DENY is a clear negative outcome. A DENY that is suppressed is not an affirmative ALLOW — it simply removes that policy's objection and lets lower-priority policies weigh in. If no further policies match after a suppressed DENY, the result is NO_DECISION.

All conditions within unless are AND'd — all must be true for the unless to trigger.

