2.5 Action Block

Defines what happens when the policy blocks access. Currently supports a message field. Designed to be extensible for future actions (notifications, webhooks, etc.).

The action block is only applied when the policy's effective result is a block — either a DENY decision (with no unless block, or with an unless block that was not triggered), or an ALLOW decision inverted by a triggered unless. When a policy results in an ALLOW or a suppressed DENY, the action block is ignored.

action:
  message: "Human-readable denial message."


2.7 Controls

Controls are a lightweight grouping mechanism for organizing related policies under a common regulatory or business objective. A control is its own resource — policies reference controls by fides_key.

Controls do not affect evaluation logic. They are purely organizational: for grouping policies in the UI, filtering, reporting, and auditing.

Control Schema

resource_type: control
fides_key: string          # Required. Unique identifier.
name: string               # Optional. Human-readable name.
description: string        # Optional. Purpose of the control.


