Scenario A: Declaration is for analytics.reporting with commercial tag.

Priority 500 matches → ALLOW. Done.

Scenario B: Declaration is for marketing.advertising.third_party.

Priority 500 does not match (not analytics).

Priority 200 matches, no unless → DENY. Done.

Scenario C: Declaration is for marketing.retention with user.contact.phone for customer. User is in US-NY and has opted in to marketing phone calls. marketing.retention is not tagged with commercial_classification:commercial. Ingress is from an internal CRM (not a data broker).

Priority 500 does not match (analytics.reporting ≠ marketing.retention).

Priority 200 does not match (marketing.advertising.third_party ≠ marketing.retention).

Priority 150: Block Data Broker Sources matches — marketing is a parent of marketing.retention via hierarchical matching. Unless: data_flow checks none_of: [third_party_data_broker, external_data_vendor] — ingress is from internal CRM, so condition IS met → unless triggered → DENY suppressed. Continue.

Priority 100: CCPA Sale Blocker does not match (marketing.retention is not tagged commercial). Retention Phone Access matches. Unless conditions: consent requirement not_opt_in — user has opted in, so condition is NOT met. Geo in: [US-CA, EU] — user is in US-NY, so condition is NOT met. Unless not triggered → ALLOW. Done.

Scenario D: Same as C but user is in US-CA.

Priority 150: Same as C — DENY suppressed. Continue.

Priority 100: Retention Phone Access matches. Geo condition in: [US-CA] IS met, but consent condition not_opt_in is NOT met (user opted in). Since unless conditions are AND'd and not all are met, unless is not triggered → ALLOW. Done.

Scenario E: Same as C but user has NOT opted in and is in US-CA.

Priority 150: Same as C — DENY suppressed. Continue.

Priority 100: Retention Phone Access matches. Both unless conditions met → unless triggered → decision inverts to DENY. Done.

Scenario F: Declaration is for marketing data use with user.contact.email for prospect. Ingress is from an approved vendor (not a data broker). No catch-all default policy configured.

Priority 500 does not match (analytics.reporting ≠ marketing).

Priority 200 does not match (marketing.advertising.third_party is a child of marketing, but hierarchical matching only matches parent → child, not child → parent).

Priority 150: Block Data Broker Sources matches (marketing = marketing). Unless: data_flow condition checks none_of: [third_party_data_broker, external_data_vendor] — ingress has neither, so condition IS met → unless triggered → DENY suppressed. Continue.

Priority 100: CCPA Sale Blocker does not match (not tagged commercial). Retention Phone Access does not match (requires customer subject, user.contact.phone category, and marketing.retention use).

No further policies match → NO_DECISION.

This scenario illustrates that a suppressed DENY does not produce an ALLOW — it removes the objection and defers to lower-priority policies. Without a catch-all, the result is NO_DECISION.

